# SFC — Story First Culture

# Functional Specification — MVP

**Document Version:** 0.1
**Status:** Draft
**Completion Estimate:** ~50%
**Last Updated:** 2026-07-12

---

# 1. Purpose

This document defines the functional requirements for the Minimum Viable Product (MVP) version of SFC.

The purpose of the MVP is to validate the core hypothesis:

> People want to create and consume stories using a structured multimedia format that is different from traditional social media.

The MVP should focus on:

* creator workflow,
* story creation,
* multimedia presentation,
* viewer experience.

Advanced features are intentionally excluded.

---

# 2. MVP Product Scope

## Included in MVP

The MVP must support:

* User accounts
* Creator identity
* Channels
* Series
* Seasons
* Episodes
* Pages
* Multimedia components
* Audio playback
* Canvas-based viewing
* Publishing workflow
* Public discovery
* Basic comments/reviews

---

## Excluded from MVP

The MVP will not include:

* Collaboration
* Groups
* Organizations
* Paid content
* Subscription system
* Advanced permissions
* AI creation tools
* Advanced analytics
* Marketplace features

---

# 3. User Types

---

# 3.1 Viewer

## Definition

A person who consumes SFC content.

---

## Viewer Capabilities

A Viewer can:

* browse Channels,
* search content,
* view published stories,
* play Episodes,
* play Pages,
* view individual components,
* comment,
* review,
* reply.

---

# 3.2 Creator

## Definition

An authenticated user who creates and publishes content.

---

## Creator Requirements

A Creator must:

* have an authenticated account,
* have an approved Creator identity,
* comply with SFC terms of use.

---

## Creator Capabilities

A Creator can:

* create Channels,
* create Series,
* create Episodes,
* design Pages,
* upload media,
* publish content,
* manage ownership.

---

# 4. Account Management

---

# 4.1 Account Creation

The system shall allow users to create accounts.

---

## MVP Requirement

Users must provide sufficient identity information for accountability.

Anonymous content creation is not allowed.

---

## Public Information

The following are separate:

Private identity information:

* legal/account information.

Public identity:

* Creator profile,
* Channel identity.

---

# 4.2 Creator Activation

A user must become an approved Creator before publishing content.

---

# 4.3 Channel Limits

MVP:

A Creator may own:

```text
Maximum Channels:

3
```

---

# 5. Channel Management

---

# 5.1 Create Channel

Creators can create Channels.

Required information:

* Channel name
* Description
* Category/tags
* Visibility setting
* PG rating

---

# 5.2 Channel Identity

A Channel represents the public publisher.

The Channel should contain:

* branding,
* description,
* content categories,
* published stories.

---

# 5.3 Channel States

The system shall support:

```text
Active

Archived

Deleted
```

---

# 5.4 Channel Visibility

MVP:

Supported:

```text
Public
```

Future:

```text
Private
```

---

# 6. Series Management

---

# 6.1 Create Series

A Creator can create multiple Series within a Channel.

---

## Required Information

* Title
* Description
* Tags
* Visibility
* PG rating

---

# 6.2 Empty Series

A Series may exist without Episodes.

However:

A Series cannot be published while empty.

---

# 6.3 Series Visibility

MVP supports:

```text
Public
```

Future:

```text
Restricted

Private
```

---

# 7. Season Management

---

# 7.1 Optional Seasons

Seasons are optional.

Supported structures:

Option A:

```text
Series

    Episode 1

    Episode 2
```

Option B:

```text
Series

    Season 1

        Episode 1

        Episode 2
```

---

# 8. Episode Management

---

# 8.1 Create Episode

Creators can create Episodes.

Required:

* Title
* Description
* Episode number
* PG rating

---

# 8.2 Episode States

MVP:

```text
Draft

Published

Deleted
```

---

# 8.3 Episode Publishing Requirements

An Episode can only be published if:

```text
Page 1 exists

AND

Page 1 is published
```

---

# 8.4 Episode Editing

Creators can edit published Episodes.

Editing creates a new revision.

Workflow:

```text
Published Episode

↓

Edit

↓

Revision

↓

Preview

↓

Publish Revision
```

---

# 9. Page Management

---

# 9.1 Create Page

Creators can create Pages inside Episodes.

---

# 9.2 Page Requirements

Minimum:

```text
1 Page
```

Maximum:

```text
100 Pages
```

(Configurable)

---

# 9.3 Page Ordering

Creators can reorder Pages during design.

---

# 9.4 Page Duplication

Creators can:

* duplicate Pages,
* copy Pages between Episodes.

---

# 9.5 Page Deletion

Pages may be deleted.

Deleted Pages:

* are hidden,
* are skipped during playback,
* may be restored.

---

# 10. Media Management

---

# 10.1 Supported Media Types

MVP:

* Images
* GIFs
* Video
* Audio
* Text boxes

---

# 10.2 Media Upload

Creators can upload media assets.

Uploaded media can be reused.

---

# 10.3 Media Limits

Maximum Story Components per Page:

```text
500
```

(Configurable)

---

# 11. Page Design System

---

# 11.1 Canvas

Creators design Pages using a Canvas.

---

# 11.2 Canvas Requirements

The Creator defines:

* orientation,
* size,
* component placement.

---

# 11.3 Viewer Scaling

The Viewer Canvas:

* adapts to screen size,
* maintains proportions,
* supports zoom.

---

# 11.4 Component Placement

MVP supports:

Option A:

Manual placement.

Option B:

Automatic arrangement.

---

# 12. Playback System

---

# 12.1 Playback Modes

The viewer can:

---

## Play Component

The viewer selects one component.

---

## Play Page

The current Page plays according to its timeline.

---

## Play Episode

The Episode plays sequentially.

---

# 12.2 Timeline Controls

Each component may define:

* playback order,
* start time,
* duration,
* overlap,
* effects.

---

# 12.3 Audio Playback

Pages may contain an audio track.

During Page playback:

Audio plays while visual components display.

---

# 13. Publishing Workflow

---

# 13.1 Creator Workflow

The standard workflow:

```text
Create Channel

↓

Create Series

↓

Create Season (optional)

↓

Create Episode

↓

Upload Media

↓

Create Pages

↓

Design Pages

↓

Preview

↓

Publish
```

---

# 13.2 Preview

Creators can preview:

* Pages,
* Episodes.

Deleted Pages are ignored.

---

# 13.3 Publishing

Publishing makes content available according to visibility settings.

---

# 14. Discovery

---

# 14.1 Search

Viewers can search:

* Channel name,
* Channel tags,
* Series title,
* Episode title,
* Content description.

---

# 14.2 Discovery Priority

Discovery should prioritize:

1. Channel identity
2. Story topic
3. Content quality

---

# 15. Viewer Interaction

---

# 15.1 Comments

Viewers can:

* comment,
* reply.

---

# 15.2 Reviews

Viewers may review published content.

---

# 16. Content Rating

---

# 16.1 PG Rating Requirement

Channels, Series, and Episodes must define a viewer rating.

---

# Purpose

Ratings provide:

* viewer guidance,
* parental awareness,
* content classification.

---

# 17. MVP Open Questions

The following require future decisions:

---

## Authentication

* What identity verification method?
* Manual approval or automated?

---

## Moderation

* Who reviews reported content?
* What happens after violations?

---

## Search

* Keyword only?
* Tags?
* Recommendation engine?

---

## Comments

* Moderation?
* User reputation?
* Blocking?

---

## Storage

* Maximum media sizes?
* Video encoding rules?

---

## Monetization

* When introduced?
* Subscription model?
* Creator revenue?

---

# 18. MVP Success Criteria

The MVP succeeds if:

A creator can:

> Create a structured multimedia story without requiring professional video production skills.

A viewer can:

> Discover and experience a story format that feels fundamentally different from existing platforms.

